You are building PoseApp, a mobile figure drawing practice app for Android and iOS.

READ the file SPECIFICATION.md in the project root before doing any work. It is the complete app specification. Follow it precisely.

Tech stack:
- React Native with Expo SDK 54
- Expo Router for file-based navigation
- TypeScript for all code
- expo-three or react-three-fiber for 3D rendering
- i18next + expo-localization for translations
- AsyncStorage for local data persistence

Rules:
- Always use TypeScript, never plain JavaScript.
- Use Expo SDK libraries over third-party packages when possible.
- Screens go in the app/ directory (file-based routing via Expo Router).
- All user-facing strings must be externalised for localisation — never hardcode display text.
- Follow the Build Phases section of the spec. Complete each phase fully before moving to the next.
- After completing work, briefly state what was done and what the next step is.
